			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Here's a little test for some of you to try out.  Perhaps it's a bit of a bug.  =)  But a COOL one if so.  Get a sow first.  Charm a blue or even con, then attack another blue or even con.  Try to use a low level charm spell or maybe all of them you have one at a time.  Also stay near a zone.  But after you have charmed one pet, wait a bit and charm the one that he is attacking and wait.  It says you can only have one pet at a time on the screen.  But you might be surprised if when the first charm comes off, the second one takes over.  =)  I believe the charm spell actually sticks to the other mob yet is just dormant, and when the other pet's charm comes off, it comes undormant.  It may not work all the time because it may be dormant for 10 seconds and that may be the total length of time the charm spell sticks or would have stuck if you didn't have a pet already.  Give it a try, have some fun. <BR>
<BR>
One other suggestion I have is making shortcut buttons.  Specifically 2 of them are most important.  1)  Pet attack and 2)  Pet guard here.  Once you've charmed one mob, if two of them are together, you can quickly(while running backwards) target the other one and hit the &quot;pet attack&quot; button.  Now when the fight is almost over, be ready to hit pet guard here and run out of distance, memorize your strip enchantment spell, remove all the buffs from your pet(including charm) and root him.  You want to remove his charm fast, otherwise he'll regain HP's...which is no good.
				</font>
			</td>

