			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				you can't recharm a mob while your current charm is active. Create some logs to find the max duration of your charm spell. I'd suggest low greens near a zone line. After you have a good idea of the max duration, charm a low green and then recast charm halfway thru the duration. You'll find that the duration never exceeds the maximuum from the first charm you cast.<BR>
<BR>
It makes no sense for verant to allow you to recharm a mob. The risk/reward balance would be way off since charmed mobs are much more powerful than all other pets and you could indefinetly sustain the charm with almost no risk.
				</font>
			</td>

