			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have around 117 CHA (I didnt know what an ENC needed when I made him!) But I have no prob with Charm durations, it depends on the Caster's CHA and the Mob, (i.e. Even Sarnaks aren't charmable!)<BR>
<BR>
I managed to use Beguile on a Giant Tump in Frontier Mountains (Kunark) and I believe I had him charmed to the very max of Beguile. The VERY important part of charming is the CHA, and Tashani. You need someone to distract the mob (i.e. Tank!), Use Tashani, then Beguile and you got yourself a Temp Pet to help your Tank, when the battle is done and you believe your pet wont break anytime soon, Re-beguile him and he's your pet for a shorter duration.<BR>
<BR>
NOTE: You can re-beguile your Pet before he breaks, But the new charm WILL ALWAYS be shorter than if he was a new mob, only re-charm if you are in a long fight and dont want any blood on your Camp. :)<BR>
<BR>
Nendidar<BR>
29th Circle Enchanter.<BR>
Xev Server <BR>

